Ad Text:
How do we teach thinking in the age of commoditized intelligence? 


Our Australia-based AI-first Ed-Tech is solving this!

Mission-driven Ed-Tech sector leader

LLM / NLP / AI production systems

Sydney Head office / hybrid / remote

Decades-long university partnerships / established market player

An exciting opportunity now exists to join one of the fastest growing and most innovative companies in the dynamic education technology sector - Studiosity.

Now reaching over 1.8 million students across the UK, USA, Canada, Australia, NZ, UAE and beyond – Studiosity is the premium partner of choice amongst educational institutions.

This makes us uniquely positioned to win and keep growing our mission to be able to enable better learning experiences and equal opportunity for students.




What you will do

Reporting to the Head of AI, you will join our Product Platform team as an experienced AI Engineer, leading the experimentation, design and development of market-leading generative AI education solutions. Your work will directly support our mission to improve life chances for students everywhere.

This role places you at the forefront of defining how the next generation learns - inventing new ways for students to interact with knowledge, practice skills, and receive personalised feedback.

A critical part of your work will be evolving our AI guardrails and quality systems, ensuring that all AI-generated feedback is safe, ethical, pedagogically sound, and supporting learning outcomes. Our AI team works closely with our Academic Standards team to ensure we focus on the high educational standards. You’ll help shape not only the product experience, but also the principles and practices that underpin responsible AI in education.




About you

You are an experienced AI Engineer with strong foundations in machine learning, software engineering, and modern generative AI techniques. 

You will ideally have:

3+ years of experience designing, building, and operating scalable AI pipelines across data collection, evaluation, deployment, and monitoring.

2+ years of commercial experience working on NLP, large language models, or document understanding/analysis applications.

Strong understanding of machine learning fundamentals, model evaluation, data preprocessing, and robust software engineering practices.

Experience developing intelligent search systems and/or anomaly detection algorithms is a plus. 

Experience with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, GCP, or Azure) and associated AI/ML services.

A demonstrated ability and enthusiasm for mentoring and guiding engineers, fostering growth and technical excellence across the team.

Demonstrated active use of modern AI tools in the development process is expected. 

Experienced with Python.




Why Studiosity?

Studiosity is an amazing place to work: In addition to our noble purpose of increasing life chances for students, we benefit from a low ego, non-corporate and lifestyle-friendly work ethic and culture. These are complemented by an exceptional passion and drive for lifelong learning in which everyone stays results-driven and proud of the work we deliver every day.


To express your interest please forward a cover letter accompanied by your current resume. Thanks for your consideration and we look forward to hearing from you.

Ad Text:
Salary: $77,000 - $80,000 + Super (negotiable based on experience)

About Us:

Kingsford Academy Australia is a registered multi-campus RTO delivering nationally recognised qualifications. We operate a technology-driven training environment with Moodle LMS, Office 365, Azure-hosted web systems and Active Directory (hybrid), on-premise NAS storage, internal IT-managed website services, AI-enhanced online learning platforms, as well as centrally managed VOIP and Wi-Fi Systems.

We are seeking a skilled ICT Support Engineer to support, maintain, test, and enhance our ICT infrastructure, LMS and student systems, support multi-campus operations, and contribute to IT solution testing and deployment across multiple campuses.

About the Role:

This is a specialised, ongoing role responsible for the engineering, maintenance, and testing of complex ICT systems and infrastructure within a Registered Training Organisation (RTO). The position involves designing, supporting, and optimising hybrid ICT environments, including learning management systems, web platforms, and cloud-hosted and on-premises infrastructure. The role supports academic staff, trainers, administrative staff, and students, and plays a critical role in ensuring the availability, security, performance, and continuous improvement of education-critical ICT systems and digital learning platforms.

 

Eligibility requirement: Applicants must be Australian citizens or permanent residents.

Key Responsibilities:

·         Design, configure, deploy, and optimise hybrid ICT infrastructure, including cloud-hosted and on-premises servers, storage, network systems, and identity/access management

·         Lead the planning, deployment, testing, and validation of learning management systems (LMS), student management systems (SMS), and other educational software, including creating test plans, documenting results, and implementing improvements and upgrades.

·         Analyse complex ICT issues, perform root-cause analysis, and implement engineering solutions to improve system efficiency, reliability, and security.

·         Develop, maintain, and optimise technical documentation, including SOPs, change logs, test results, asset lifecycle records, and deployment plans

·         Implement, monitor, and improve cybersecurity frameworks, including access controls, threat protection, patching, and vulnerability management in line with compliance standards

·         Lead digitalisation and online content deployment, including learning materials and sample solutions

·         Plan, deploy, and optimise multi-campus ICT infrastructure, including network systems, collaboration tools, and peripheral devices

·         Maintain backup, recovery, and business continuity processes across all educational systems

·         Support and optimise virtual learning environments, lab setups, and student practice platforms

·         Conduct system upgrades, migrations, and optimisations with minimal disruption to academic operations

·         Monitor ticketing workflows, escalations, and resolution of complex ICT issues handled by the internal IT team

·         Provide training for staff, trainers, and students on ICT systems, digital platforms, and workflows to enhance user competency and adoption

·         Provide strategic input for ICT system improvements, infrastructure planning, and automation initiatives

·         Collaborate with academic and IT teams to integrate new digital tools and internal solutions to support teaching and learning innovation

Skills & Experience:

Essential:

·         The candidate must hold an Australian Bachelor's or higher qualification in ICT.

·         Minimum 2+ years’ experience in ICT support engineering or system support roles with engineering-level responsibilities

·         Experience in design, deployment, testing, and optimisation of ICT systems

·         Strong understanding of hybrid infrastructure, on-premises servers, networking, and identity/access management

·         Hands-on experience managing learning management systems and student management platforms

·         Demonstrated ability in troubleshooting complex technical issues, root-cause analysis, and system improvements

·         Experience documenting test plans, technical procedures, change logs, and incident reports

·         Strong analytical and problem-solving skills

·         Excellent communication skills to support technical and non-technical stakeholders

Desirable:

·         Experience with Azure, Office 365 administration, and cloud platform integration.

·         Exposure to NAS storage, backup/recovery systems, cybersecurity controls, and compliance practices.

·         Prior experience in RTO or educational IT environments.

·         Relevant ICT qualifications or certifications (e.g., Microsoft, Cisco, CompTIA).

·         Familiarity with IT project participation, testing environments, and system improvement initiatives.




 

Why Work With Us?

·         Engage in a hands-on engineering and testing role managing hybrid IT infrastructure across multiple campuses.

·         Work on system deployment, software testing, diagnostics, and continuous improvement projects.

·         Exposure to cloud platforms, on-prem infrastructure, Moodle LMS, AI-based learning tools, and multi-campus IT operations.

·         Opportunity to participate in IT development projects, infrastructure upgrades, and automation initiatives.

·         Contribute to a modern, technology-driven education environment with long-term growth potential and professional development.

·         Be part of a highly technical team supporting critical IT operations and educational innovation.

How to Apply?

Please submit your resume along with a brief cover letter outlining your experience and suitability for this role. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Job Title: Staff Software Engineer - AI Powered Engineering
Ad Text:
Staff Software Engineer - AI Powered Engineering 

**Sydney or Melbourne locations**

Engineer the future of software delivery at Australia’s largest bank!

We’re building the next generation of AI-powered engineering capabilities at CommBank—tools and platforms that materially improve how thousands of engineers build, ship, and operate software.

If you’re a technical lead who thrives in complex environments, enjoys working across many stakeholders, and is curious about how AI can responsibly uplift engineering productivity, this role is for you.




Do work that matters

You’ll be part of the AI Powered Engineering function, whose mandate is clear: Responsibly embed AI-assisted tools and capabilities that improve developer experience, delivery velocity, and software quality across the bank.

This is not a data science role. It’s about engineering systems, platforms, and workflows that integrate AI into real-world software delivery—safely, pragmatically, and at enterprise scale.




About the team

We’re a hands-on, product-minded engineering team operating at the intersection of:

Platform engineering

Developer productivity

Applied AI & AI Ops

We experiment, validate, and scale AI-enabled capabilities such as:

AI-powered engineering tools (e.g. Patchwork, Project Coral, Roo Code)

Knowledge assistants for internal engineering and compliance information

Automation for API documentation, controls, and compliance workflows

AI Ops solutions in partnership with Cyber teams (e.g. incident response support)




Everything we build is grounded in safety, reliability, and measurable impact.

What you’ll do

As a Staff Software Engineer, you’ll operate as a senior technical leader and multiplier:

Collaborate on complex technical problems from discovery through to production.

Translate business and engineering needs into clear technical designs and delivery plans.

Experiment with AI, GenAI, and automation tools—running fit-for-purpose evaluations and sharing grounded recommendations.

Design and deliver resilient, reusable services and components that integrate into existing platforms and pipelines.

Contribute to architecture discussions and role-model engineering best practices.

Maintain high-quality codebases through active code reviews and documentation.

Work across a broad stakeholder landscape (often 50+ stakeholders) to align roadmaps and land change with minimal disruption.

Provide technical guidance and mentorship to engineers, uplifting engineering craft and AI literacy across teams.

What you bring

Technical capability

Extensive experience as a software engineer with proficiency in one or more of: Python, Java, C#, TypeScript, Node.js

Experience building and operating microservices and event-driven systems.

Cloud experience with AWS, Azure, or GCP (e.g. Lambda/Functions, ECS/AKS, API Gateway, Step Functions).

Familiarity with:

REST and/or gRPC APIs

SQL and data pipelines

Observability and engineering productivity metrics

Strong DevSecOps practices:

CI/CD (GitHub, GitLab, Azure DevOps)

Infrastructure as Code (Terraform)

Secure software supply chain practices (SAST/DAST/SCA, secrets management)

Desirable

Exposure to API or AI developer tools (e.g. Roo Code, Claude, CLI-based tools).

Familiarity with cybersecurity frameworks such as NIST.

Experience partnering with Cyber or Risk teams on secure engineering initiatives.

If this sounds like you, apply today.

We support flexibility with a hybrid approach—at least half your time each month connecting in office—plus options such as adjusted start/finish times, part‑time, and job share

Their focus isn’t on simply scaling bigger models, but on building systems that can reason, act, and persist over time.

They don’t care about degrees, titles or pedigree — what matters is capability. If you can reason deeply, move fast and push technical boundaries, you’ll thrive there. Those with a Mathematics background will be highly regarded.

This is not a maintenance role — you’ll be building the backbone of their cognition stack, enabling researchers to move faster and scale experiments more effectively.

You’ll work directly with the founder and senior scientists to design and implement the infrastructure that underpins their approach to agentic AI. The scope spans distributed training pipelines, high-performance compute orchestration, and building tools that streamline research workflows.

Strong background in distributed systems, cloud platforms, and infrastructure at scale

Familiarity with containerisation, orchestration (Kubernetes, Docker), and CI/CD pipelines

Why This Role
This is a chance to be the engineer building the foundations for some of the most ambitious work happening in AI right now. You’ll work closely with the founder, help shape the technical direction of the lab, and have a direct hand in enabling breakthroughs in agentic AI.
